[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating server connection behavior**\n\nI’m thinking about whether to keep the coverage for each dynamic-access class in separate Java test files, which seems like a good move. I’m mapping the class names and paths correctly, but there’s a potential issue with the fake server only handling one socket at a time. I wonder about possible deadlocks, since the server accepts connections until EOF, but during this, it’s blocked. Still, if everything is handled correctly, it seems manageable. I'll continue confirming these points!\n\n**Analyzing connection handling**\n\nI'm noticing a potential issue where `connection.close()` on the wrapper returns the object to the pool without closing the underlying connection, which means the server remains blocked until `pool.close()`. That seems fine for now. I also see that calling `connection.setTimeout(COMMAND_TIMEOUT);` before checking `isOpen` could affect the flow. I should validate the version in the POM file, even if it may not be necessary. For now, version 2.11.1 with lettuce 6.2.6 looks like it could work!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b95b9ca34006193016a234fbfbf2081978ea3d1bef5b5e532\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqI0_QYlFYApcwSLpfN2XPw6jexDWeSUgxMu8N4o4Akj9IAH-c3IXEYicjtlJJQPFMie8aL6vKUG-rOODzBMctdKynlSZXSzuRR5GHHGMbI7EyVJQFRHvEncJk6OEs4cK4SV9VlCo4q25h0mWqwBb-EkyT9AnNKtZZFNGHmVinRxukwbHHEZkR5inoQ8k2y-YuSUmYH9AN2-Wzk8yX31dDU2cLukT9I2pK4JQMd3lrBJyxVsHRb7sj4nEGgOYC6pECyzIZJGs2WOVe7QfRDA0XGE02yW6wfeVVKEm1LFsLS-beMSoS5VAl0RzUsNOA910Iyv9z4hhJmaHuPPseMevu3zow3Q-lDcRD5Xx6G-hB6MSagln7ivzPQIPbu1d7ElA1MgWjgTyP7B_yfckbBke_4lXfimWg5JM9pc7OgSPvvs5j8mjQ8rqyeNGPJnNCALcIKGcvTGlYNeXNKOSzNgUDrkqrP4g5yQCSVRBj52ffSzyLmxWubBx5RAasrrdwuKHJt3QsvJgQrvruM3PQu0aXa7yRKZ1g1Ety0Y5_6D2OisdEV8EU_fkslifEk3TRsqOAMp5IMWaWg0_RP_wXIbNYvxI_alvEPvQJjaC6lN7Ht5Rv196YXdh44UR2OpaexmEEYjeBelpiWCk7aodrjowfVe